Differential Diagnosis.
Larger than the other two members of the group (ca. 1.97 vs. 
1.70 mm
), and with the lateral margins of the pronotum slightly more arcuate. The aedeagus differs in several respects from that of the other two species, including the main piece process having two short sharp points at the apex (
Fig. 27
).
